# Documentation sync (mandatory on domain changes)

When you change **Prisma schema**, **migrations**, **backend modules**, **API routes**, or **ship a slice**, update the matching docs in the **same PR/task** — do not leave docs stale.

## Doc map

| File | Update when |
|------|-------------|
| `apps/backend/prisma/schema.prisma` | Source of truth — change code first |
| `DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` | Any model/enum/field/index/FK/semantic change |
| `CURRENT_ARCHITECTURE.md` | New module, flow, integration, API area, or known inconsistency fixed |
| `PRODUCT_OVERVIEW.md` | Slice done, progress tracker, route inventory, feature status |
| `SLICE-NN-*.md` | New slice spec or marking slice complete |
| `apps/backend/*.md` | Module-specific deep-dive (`GENERATION.md`, `COUNCIL.md`, etc.) when behavior changes |

## Checklist — schema / migration

1. Edit `schema.prisma` + add migration.
2. Update `DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`: affected table(s), enum values, relations, caveats, "Last synced" line.
3. If architecture-level impact (new entity, dropped table, tenancy change): update `CURRENT_ARCHITECTURE.md`.
4. Run tests; note breaking API changes in slice or overview doc.

## Checklist — new slice / feature

1. Create or update `SLICE-NN-feature.md` at repo root.
2. Mark progress in `PRODUCT_OVERVIEW.md` (tracker + module status table).
3. Add routes/modules to `CURRENT_ARCHITECTURE.md` if user-facing.
4. Add tables/fields to `DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` if schema changed.

## Field documentation style (`DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`)

Per table: field name, type, null, default, one-line **what it stores** and **who writes it** (module/service). Flag dead enums and denormalized fields.

## Do not

- Document planned schema that is not in `schema.prisma`.
- Duplicate full enum lists in `CURRENT_ARCHITECTURE.md` — link to `DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` instead.
- Skip doc updates because the change "feels small".
